            <title>[KAFKA-2775] Copycat exceptions should be in api package so they can be caught by user code without any dependencies other than api</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-2775</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Some of these were created in runtime because that&apos;s where the code that used them originated, but locating them there requires depending on the entire runtime jar. Instead, we should have a set of exceptions defined in the API that users can both rely on and use in their own code without additional dependencies.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
